cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.AR 

Reasoning: The paper deals with the design of a network that can provide bounded-delay guarantees for packets. This falls under the category of networked systems and protocols, which is covered by cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the necessary and sufficient conditions for deterministic bounded-delays in the network, which involves information theory and communication theory, covered by cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also mentions that the proposed solution does not require any changes in the core of the network, which relates to distributed computing, covered by cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the design of a novel solution, which involves architecture and implementation, covered by cs.AR (Hardware Architecture).
